{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "615454d735c498fd4574c8e3", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": null, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": null, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "NTAS1", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76e4c52ffa3c944600e1"], "subjects": ["615d70bd9948bc1b21da2b1f"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6ebab"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [{"title": "NTA Abhyas Paper", "value": "116", "isVisible": true}], "previousYearPapers": [], "question": {"text": "Calculate the ionisation energy of sodium in <math> <mrow> <msup> <mrow> <mtext>kJ&nbsp;mol</mtext></mrow> <mrow> <mo>\u2212</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow> </msup> </mrow> </math> if electromagnetic&nbsp;radiation of wavelength <math> <mrow> <mn>242</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mtext>nm</mtext></mrow> </math> is just sufficient to ionise the sodium atom.", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "E11JP", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>946</mn><mo>\u00d7</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}, {"id": "GtqWf", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>946</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></msup></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "ksW33", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>946</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>4</mn></msup></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "Ajz0G", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>946</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "<p>Ionisation energy is the amount of energy required to remove most loosely bound electron from